## Styling and CSS Management

* **Prefer Tailwind CSS** for styling
* Avoid redundant custom styles; **leverage Tailwind's utility classes** as much as possible
* Keep Tailwind classes scoped within components for style encapsulation
* If Tailwind cannot meet complex styling needs, **supplement with Less**
* Use Less for theming, color overrides, and variable customization (e.g., customizing Ant Design Vue theme variables)
* Name style files using `.module.less` (if using CSS Modules) or `.less` for standard usage
* Avoid global styles when possible; favor modular and scoped styling

## UI Component Library (Ant Design Vue)

* Use [Ant Design Vue (ant-design-vue)](https://www.antdv.com/) as the primary UI component library
* **Use on-demand importing** to reduce bundle size
* Prefer built-in components (e.g., form, table, modal) from the library instead of custom implementations
* Style overrides should be handled through Less variables or `:deep` with Tailwind for minimal adjustments
* Follow Ant Design Vue's [official best practices](https://www.antdv.com/components/overview/) when using components
* For advanced use cases, **wrap and extend components** instead of modifying core styles directly
* Maintain UI consistency across the app by using unified components (e.g., always use `a-button` rather than mixing buttons from different libraries)

